player.seasonOutlook: The cool kids (Cooper Kupp, included) call him "Bobby Trees," but for our purposes, Woods can be called an aging depth contributor buried behind younger and more productive receivers as he heads into another season. Of the 115 receivers with at least 30 targets last season, Woods' 5.5 yards per target ranked 105th, confirming the low ceiling in place for this clubhouse presence. Fantasy managers should avoid Woods on draft day.
